{"questionId":"22192","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A particle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> moves along the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis. The velocity of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> seconds,&nbsp;where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>3</mn></math>. When <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>P</mi></math> is at the origin <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that the distance of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math> at this time is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>88</mn><mn>27</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;metres.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to integrate&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∫</mo><mi>v</mi><mo> </mo><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>∫</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></